The name “Five Element Flow” comes from a philosophy in Tai Chi called Five Element Theory. The general idea is balancing five natural elements: Wood (green), Water (blue), Fire (red), Earth (yellow), and Metal (white). It could be really cool to include a representation of each element in the logo, but this is not a requirement. I really love nature themes, but I want to prioritize a very clear logo rather than crowding it with lots of elements. I’m also a huge fan of Avatar: The Last Airbender and other nerdy things. I’m looking for a logo that will convey that my business is not a typical martial arts or yoga school. Most martial arts schools in the area go for more aggressive designs, which is not my style. I’m looking for a much more meditative and spiritual message. My classes are self-defense oriented, but it is much more about building connections between people than fighting.
